# CropAbility test rules

Full guide: **`doc/TESTING.md`** (do not duplicate as README under `src/test/`).

## Location

- All Python tests: **`src/test/python/`** only.
- Shared fixtures: `conftest.py`.
- No `scripts/` for checks; no `src/test/rust/` package.

## Markers (`pyproject.toml`)

| Marker | Use |
|--------|-----|
| `native` | Needs `cropability.native._core` (after `maturin develop --features python,htslib`) |
| `gpu` | Needs CUDA |
| `slow` | Long benchmarks (reserved) |

## File map

| File | Tests |
|------|--------|
| `test_config.py` | `utils.config` |
| `test_gpu_manager.py` | `gpu.device_manager` |
| `test_kernels_seq.py` / `test_kernels_stats.py` | `kernels.*` (CPU ok) |
| `test_genomics.py` | GPU `genomics/*` (CPU ok) |
| `test_ngs_io.py` | `ngs.io` — VCF pure Python; FASTA `@pytest.mark.native` |
| `test_ngs_pipeline.py` | `ngs.pipeline`, BAM — module `importorskip` + `native` mark |
| `test_cli.py` | CLI parsing (no `export` subcommand) |

## Adding tests

- Import from **`cropability.ngs`**, not deprecated `cropability.io` / `genomics.pipeline`.
- Heavy GPU work: `@pytest.mark.gpu` and skip when no CUDA.
- Do not add TorchScript round-trip or `.pt` export tests unless product scope changes.
